rComments: Nara is honestly a really good lecturer despite the accent. She really knows her stuff. She is very passionate and tries to explain things in great detail. Definitely will take her class again!

rComments: Horrible accent. Very disorganized during lecture. Not qualified to be a lecturer imo.

She is the greatest prof have I had in my second year. The way she makes a test is clearly showed by past tests and she does not make tricky questions. I lf you do the homework she post in syllabus at the beginning of the semester you will get 75+ on test.
Terrible prof. The language barrie made it really hard to understand any concepts!

Horrible lecturer. She can barely speak English despite being hired solely to teach the course. She reviewed the hardest part of the course in a single lecture and made the exam on it

As a course coordinator, she was terrible. Her midterms can be quite difficult and will posts questions on the midterm or final when you did not really see the questions in the textbook even if you do more than what she asks. Her lecture are not useful and has a language barrier. The language barrier is one of the reason her tests are difficult.

Honestly a very caring prof. She goes too fast in her notes and its sometimes hard to understand the calculus because you are too busy trying to catch up with her notes rather than understand them. Fairly easy. Agreed to others saying she does not make sense sometimes. A little bit disorganized, but she is passionate. Better attend the class to take notes, and it will be okay.
